[Equity Transfer Agreement]

34
00:02:51,761 --> 00:02:53,216
I've taken back the dock.

35
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,600
Got anything else to say?

36
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,456
Congrats, An Ning.

37
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:05,776
You got the dock back.

38
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,696
Your father-in-law will be thrilled.

39
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:09,456
I'll throw a party for you.

40
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,760
To celebrate your great success.

41
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:19,457
Mom.

42
00:03:19,481 --> 00:03:20,736
No matter how capable she is,

43
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:23,256
she's just a dog we keep.

44
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,616
No need to suck up to her.

45
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:27,200
I didn't expect her to get the dock back.

46
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:29,176
For now, we can only placate her.

47
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,097
Then figure out the next move.

48
00:03:30,121 --> 00:03:31,480
Her good days won't last long.

49
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,216
Soon, I'll prove

50
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,920
she's not An Ning at all.

51
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:39,600
Even Rong from the Qingyun Gang
confirmed she's not Ye Ying.

52
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,496
Why do you still insist on staying here?

53
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:42,760
She is Ye Ying.

54
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:48,480
The way of checking the bullet
by flicking the cylinder

55
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,280
is only a skill honed since childhood.

56
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,656
Even if she's lost her memory,

57
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,936
those habits built over the years

58
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:59,096
are already etched deep in her bones.

59
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,696
So once Ye Ying regains her memory,

60
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,760
we can get the password
for the flash drive.

61
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:06,080
But everyone in this house
wants her dead.

62
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:11,640
Ye Ying.

63
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,280
I gotta get her, no matter what.

64
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:24,480
Miss.

65
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,600
Miss.

66
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:28,400
You're finally back.

67
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:29,776
Tell me, in this world,

68
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:32,080
can two people really look
that much alike?

69
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:40,336
I look just like
the Ye family's Young Lady.

70
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,936
And Rong seems so certain about it.

71
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:44,480
Could I really be Ye Ying?

72
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,696
Make sure to tell the family doctor.

73
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,816
When An Ning gets home,

74
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,936
you must say it's just a check-up.

75
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:55,400
Never let her know
it's a blood test for DNA.

76
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:59,056
If it's really a DNA test,

77
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,640
I'm afraid I can't avoid it.

78
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,256
If they find out I'm not An Ning,

79
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:13,936
they'll act even more recklessly.

80
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,776
And definitely kill me.

81
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,096
Then they'll claim An Ning is dead

82
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,400
and seize her shares.

83
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,696
So I gotta get An Ning's blood sample
to replace mine.

84
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,400
It's the only way to survive this.

85
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:31,336
Lately, reports against the Song Group
keep showing up.

86
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,536
Our three batches of goods
have been inspected already.

87
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:34,816
The weapons hidden inside

88
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,296
were almost discovered.

89
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,320
Don't worry.

90
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,616
Send me the list of inspectors
who seized the goods.

91
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,040
I'll handle them one by one.

92
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:43,920
Weapons.

93
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,016
So Song Pa was secretly
involved in gang crime.

94
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,480
His business is illegal.

95
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,400
Inspector Jiang, you're reliable.

96
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:55,616
Huo Xiao may say yes on the surface.

97
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:58,040
But he doesn't really intend to help me.

98
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,096
Huo Xiao is a schemer.

99
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,856
We've worked together at the station for
years.

100
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:04,280
But I still can't figure him out.

101
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:05,880
You need to be careful.

102
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:10,176
But the higher-ups
handed the report case to Huo Xiao.

103
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,360
I need to keep him steady.

104
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,816
Let him stay at my place.

105
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,216
Keep him right under my nose.

106
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,720
Better than him hiding in the shadows.

107
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,736
Turns out Huo Xiao never
teamed up with Song Pa.

108
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:21,376
The dirty cop Song Pa bought

109
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,600
is Officer Jiang.

110
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,376
Leave this to me.

111
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,400
You go first.

112
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,296
Your toy car.

113
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,296
You blocked my car just now, didn't you?

114
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:56,056
I'll have my grandpa
chop you into tiny pieces.

115
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,760
And dump you in the river for the fish.

116
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,816
Who does your grandpa think he is?

117
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,696
Daring to talk big here.

118
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,280
I could end you right now.

119
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,440
Jiang Meng.

120
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:20,400
You've done plenty of rotten things.

121
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,960
Now you even target little kids.

122
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:26,400
Since when did Inspector Huo
become a hero of justice?

123
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:27,920
Shall we see

124
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,920
if your gun is faster than mine?

125
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,520
Even fate wanted him dead.

126
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,800
Not my fault.

127
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,336
It's a pneumothorax.

128
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,136
It's windy here.

129
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,200
Let's take him home first.

130
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:06,936
Baby.

131
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:07,960
What's wrong, baby?

132
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:08,496
Baby.

133
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:08,936
What happened?

134
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,656
Baby.

135
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,360
What's happening to you?

136
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,160
Baby.

137
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,480
What's going on?

138
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,160
An Ning.

139
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,320
What's wrong with my son?

140
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,240
Why did you hurt my son?

141
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,776
You cruel woman.

142
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,136
Trying to harm my grandson.

143
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,336
I'll tear your face off!

144
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,400
I didn't do anything!

145
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:23,857
He got a fright.

146
00:08:23,881 --> 00:08:25,216
It's a spontaneous pneumothorax.

147
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,016
Call an ambulance now.

148
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,160
I know to call an ambulance.

149
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:28,360
Don't need you to tell me.

150
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:29,137
Ti Cha.

151
00:08:29,161 --> 00:08:30,600
Hurry, make the call.

152
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,960
Wake up, baby. Mommy's right here.

153
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,576
Is this the emergency center?

154
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,120
Someone here needs urgent help!

155
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,137
Fifteen minutes

156
00:08:40,161 --> 00:08:41,496
is the fastest?

157
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:42,520
Fifteen minutes.

158
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,720
No way.

159
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,200
Fifteen minutes is too long.

160
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,800
He can't breathe.

161
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,016
A few more minutes...

162
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,040
He's about to die.

163
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,000
Baby.

164
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:54,056
What... what are you doing?

165
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,480
Baby, wake up, baby.

166
00:08:58,720 --> 00:08:59,720
You... you...

167
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:00,840
What are you doing?

168
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:05,817
Cruel woman.

169
00:09:05,841 --> 00:09:07,616
Daring to kill him right in front of me?

170
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:09,416
If you touch my nephew again,

171
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,137
then I'll

172
00:09:10,161 --> 00:09:11,601
send you straight to hell right now!

173
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,040
It's too late now!

174
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,040
If we don't save him soon,

175
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,057
he'll really die!

176
00:09:15,081 --> 00:09:16,096
You're full of talk.

177
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,216
Who do you think you are?

178
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,576
How dare you say you can save him?

179
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,960
You're clearly trying to harm him!

180
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,137
Xiao.

181
00:09:22,161 --> 00:09:23,360
Arrest her now.

182
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,057
You got a plan?

183
00:09:26,081 --> 00:09:27,480
I have to give it a try.

184
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:31,457
Everyone, get out.

185
00:09:31,481 --> 00:09:32,576
This...

186
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,816
This is a matter of life and death.

187
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,840
I said, out!

188
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,377
Dad.

189
00:09:38,401 --> 00:09:40,120
Why should we listen to him?

190
00:09:40,121 --> 00:09:50,295
Officail Website : dramacool.club  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

191
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,320
Just go out first.

192
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,680
Dad.

193
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,080
Lend me your lighter.

194
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,760
Undo his shirt.

195
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:36,657
Hurry, hurry up.

196
00:10:36,681 --> 00:10:37,760
- Hurry.
- Take it easy.

197
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,936
- Move slow.
- Come on, hurry.

198
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,976
- Hurry.
- Slow down.

199
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,000
Watch out.

200
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,816
Slow down.

201
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:44,816
Can you go any faster?

202
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,840
Take it easy.

203
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:46,857
Doctor,

204
00:10:46,881 --> 00:10:48,056
how's my grandson?

205
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,976
A spontaneous pneumothorax
caused by extreme tension.

206
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,777
In cases like this,

207
00:10:50,801 --> 00:10:53,121
there's often only four or five minutes
to save the person.

208
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:55,416
This lady's first aid method was spot on.

209
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,896
She used a pen cartridge
as an oxygen tube

210
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,976
to get oxygen into the boy's lung.

211
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,000
Otherwise,

212
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,640
he wouldn't have made it until we came.

213
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,936
You were brave back there.

214
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,656
But scared now?

215
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,680
I'm not scared.

216
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,280
The wind's too strong.

217
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:18,040
Does it hurt?

218
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,600
How did you know I'd save him?

219
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:25,376
Do you think I can't tell

220
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,256
who genuinely wanted to

221
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:28,320
save that kid?

222
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,440
What if...

223
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,760
What if I couldn't save him?

224
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:37,856
What if I failed?

225
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:38,880
There's no "what ifs".

226
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,120
Even if there were,

227
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,520
I'd face the consequences with you.

228
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:50,200
I thought

229
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,416
you were covering for Song Pa
and his family's wrongdoings.

230
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,240
Turns out the real dirty cop
was someone else.

231
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,336
But if it's not about Song Pa,

232
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,856
why are you staying here?

233
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:00,920
And even help me when they picked on me.

234
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,097
Who are you,

235
00:13:03,121 --> 00:13:04,520
really?

236
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,320
Who I am doesn't matter.

237
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,576
What matters is

238
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:20,120
what you think of me.

239
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:38,136
Didn't expect that.

240
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,040
An Ning actually wanted to
save the baby.

241
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,416
She just got lucky.

242
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,456
But she actually managed to
save the baby.

243
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:46,320
If anything happens to the baby,

244
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,640
I'll never let her off the hook.

245
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:49,856
Miss.

246
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:50,536
Madam.

247
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,600
The family doctor is here.

248
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,377
Let him go for now.

249
00:13:53,401 --> 00:13:54,416
No need to fuss today.

250
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,256
Yes.

251
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:56,280
Wait.

252
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,360
Mom.

253
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:02,800
Did An Ning get her hand cut by a pen

254
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,480
and bleed today?

255
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,696
You... you...

256
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:08,720
What are you doing?

257
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:16,337
Mom.

258
00:14:16,361 --> 00:14:17,536
Don't you remember?

259
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,040
An Ning faints at the sight of blood.

260
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,200
But today, she saw blood

261
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:24,560
and didn't react at all.

262
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,320
You mean...

263
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:32,856
This woman is definitely
hiding something.

264
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:33,880
Steward.

265
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,376
Go tell the family doctor.

266
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,816
Have An Ning

267
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,056
get a blood test right away.

268
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,080
Yes.

269
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:44,800
An Ning, open the door!

270
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:46,856
I'm warning you, you troublemaker.

271
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:47,577
Open the door now!

272
00:14:47,601 --> 00:14:48,896
If I break it down, - Open it now!

273
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,000
You'll regret it even more!

274
